<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4984&amp;p=44683#p44683"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[CHR-ROM + RAM on the same cartrige possible?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4984&amp;p=44683#p44683"><![CDATA[
The N106 allows for both CHR ROM and CHR RAM. One can select 4k CHR banks, and 2 of those 4k pages are CHR RAM. Though I recently read that this mapper is nearly impossible to make a dev cartridge out of, because all of the chips are glob-tops.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=138">Celius</a> — Tue Mar 24, 2009 10:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
