<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[bunnyboy]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-03-24T06:32:42-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-03-24T06:32:42-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4984&amp;p=44678#p44678</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4984&amp;p=44678#p44678"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[CHR-ROM + RAM on the same cartrige possible?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4984&amp;p=44678#p44678"><![CDATA[
Pin Bot and High Speed use an upper CHR address line from the MMC3 as the ROM/RAM select, so the board should do 128KB of each after rewriring.  As is the board only does 64KB because it uses the 28 pin ROM.  RAM can be banked just like the ROM.  I would guess the games use it for animated tiles, but it isn't a common board so there should be a pretty good reason to use it if you plan on real hardware.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=228">bunnyboy</a> — Tue Mar 24, 2009 6:32 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
